children.text: The water container capacity is greater than 45 litres, and there has not been adequate clearance provided between the switch/power outlet to the sink/basin.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3000 Wiring Rules states in section 6.2.2.2 that there must be 500mm clearance to the side of the water container, and 1000mm above the water container.
The location of this switch/power outlet will need to be relocated to ensure proper clearance in accordance with Australian Standard AS 3000.
